# Vibe coding template — guidance for the AI assistant

## Audience
The human using this repo is learning to build with AI and may not be technical. Prefer small, safe changes. Explain what you changed in plain language when it helps.

## Stack
- Next.js App Router (`src/app/`)
- tRPC for all server APIs (`src/server/api/routers/`)
- MongoDB via Mongoose (`src/server/db/`)
- Tailwind CSS for styling

## Secrets and environment variables
- Put API keys, database URLs, and any secret in `.env` using **server-only** names (no `NEXT_PUBLIC_` prefix).
- Never suggest exposing secrets to the browser. Client components must not read `process.env` for secrets.
- When adding a new server env var, update `src/env.js` (Zod schema + `runtimeEnv`) and `.env.example`.

## Data and backend rules
- Read and write data only from tRPC procedures (or other server-only code). Do not call the database from client components.
- Add Mongoose models under `src/server/db/models/`. Reuse models; avoid duplicating schemas.
- Add or extend routers under `src/server/api/routers/`, then register them in `src/server/api/root.ts`.
- Use Zod for procedure `input` validation. Prefer `publicProcedure` unless auth is added later.

## Frontend rules
- In Client Components, use `import { api } from "~/trpc/react"` for queries and mutations.
- In Server Components, use `import { api } from "~/trpc/server"` for calls and prefetching.
- Use Tailwind utility classes. Keep layouts readable and accessible (labels on inputs, button types, focus states).

## TypeScript and quality
- Avoid `any`. Prefer inferred types from Zod and Mongoose.
- Keep procedures focused: one clear responsibility per procedure name.
- Make minimal edits; do not refactor unrelated files.

## When the user is stuck
- Suggest they copy `.env.example` to `.env` and set `MONGODB_URI`.
- Suggest `pnpm install` and `pnpm dev` to run the app.

